<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
{{>header}}

<body>
  <!-- STYLING THE PAGE  -->

  <style>
    body {
      position: relative;
      margin: 0;
      padding-bottom: 6rem;
      min-height: 100%;
    }

    .text {
      background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.90);
      width: auto;
      border: 5px solid black;
      padding: 25px;
      margin: 20px;
    }

    .text img {
      max-width: 66%;
      max-height: auto;
      display: block;
      margin-left: auto;
      margin-right: auto;
    }

    .wrapper {
      text-align: center;
    }

    .button {
      /* position: absolute; */
      background: lightgrey;
      padding: 0.7em;
      padding: 25px;
      margin: 20px;
      width: 150px;
      border: 0;
      /* float : right; */
      display: inline-block;
    }

    .button:hover {
      background: gold;
    }

    .footer {
      position: absolute;
      right: 0;
      bottom: 0;
      left: 0;
      padding: 0.2rem;
      background-color: #efefef;
      text-align: center;
    }
  </style>

  <!-- HTML for the Instructions 2 page  -->

  <div class="text">You are about to play the second game. You are the "Human" player on the left, and you can select a
    "weapon" by clicking on
    one of the 3 icons. The computer will select a weapon of its choice as well and the results will be displayed for
    each round. The rules of the game are explained in the picture below.
    Fire beats Grass; Water beats Fire; and Grass beats Water.Your task in this game is to win as many points as
    possible against the computer.
    <br />
    <br />
    <img id="game2Rules" class="img" src="game2Rules.jpg">
    <br />
    <br />
    This second game will also have two phases. The first phase is for getting familiar with the game interface, and
    will consist of 10 trial rounds.
    After the end of this practice phase, you will be alerted to the start of the game and the scores will be
    reinitiliased at 0. You will play a total of XXX rounds of this game.
    Your computer opponent's choices in the second phase of the game are not random. They rely on rules that if
    uncovered can give you an edge in this game.
  </div>
  <div class="wrapper">
    <button class="button" id="instructions2"> Proceed to Game </button>
  </div>

  <script src="/socket.io/socket.io.js"></script>
  <script src="/js/libs/jquery-3.3.1.min.js"></script>
  <script>
    $('#instructions2').click(function () {
      window.location.href = "/game2";
    });
  </script>
  <div class="footer"> {{>footer}} </div>
</body>

</html>